            "currentCldrName": "Rooster",
            "description": "<p>A rooster (cock), a male <a href=\"/chicken/\" title=\"üêî Chicken\">chicken</a> known for its cock-a-doodle-do. Depicted as a white or multicolored rooster standing on its legs in full profile facing left, with a red <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comb_(anatomy)\">comb</a> on its head and red wattle on its neck.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not to be confused with <a href=\"/chicken/\">üêî Chicken</a>, though their applications overlap. See also <a href=\"/hatching-chick/\">üê£ Hatching Chick</a>, <a href=\"/baby-chick/\">üê§ Baby Chick</a>, and <a href=\"/front-facing-baby-chick/\">üê• Front-Facing Baby Chick</a>. Occasionally used as&nbsp;sexual slang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the 12 animals of the <a href=\"/chinese-new-year/\">Chinese zodiac</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google&rsquo;s rooster is brown with a green tail, Facebook&rsquo;s brown with a blue tail. Google&rsquo;s rooster was <a href=\"/google/android-7.0/rooster/\">previously</a> white, <a href=\"/microsoft/windows-10/rooster/\">Microsoft&rsquo;s</a> yellow, <a href=\"/samsung/experience-9.0/rooster/\">Samsung&rsquo;s</a> looking straight ahead.</p>",
